R
d:R \times R \to R
d(x,y) = |x-y|
X
f:[a,b] \to R
[a,b]
X = C[a,b]
\rho: X \times X \to R
f,g \in X
\rho(f,g) = \int_a^b \left|f(t) - g(t)\right|\;dt.
I:(X,\rho) \to (R,d)
I
I(f) = \int_a^b f(t)\;dt.
I
\epsilon > 0
\delta > 0
\rho(f,g) < \delta
d(I(f), I(g)) < \epsilon
\int_a^b\left|f(t)-g(t)\right|\;dt < \delta.
\left|\int_a^bf(t)\;dt - \int_a^bg(t)\;dt\right| < \epsilon,
\left|\int_a^b[f(t) - g(t)]\;dt\right| < \epsilon.
\left|\int_a^bf(t)\;dt\right| = \int_a^b\left|f(t)\right|\;dt
\delta = \epsilon
-|f(t)|\le f(t)\le |f(t)|
|\int_a^bf(t)dt|\le \int_a^b|f(t)|dt
